hise characters#Professor E. Gadd|Professor E. Gadd]]\n*[[Captain Olimar]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/nom/0405/1_2/|title=1-2 \u958b\u767a\u30b9\u30bf\u30c3\u30d5\u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc|publisher=Nintendo|accessdate=July 31, 2013|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n*[[Birdo]]\n*[[K.K. Slider]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{refbegin}}\n:a. {{Note|a}}Often featured as \"K.K. Song\"\n:b. {{Note|c}}The song is only present in the GameCube release of ''Pikmin 2''. It was removed in the Wii version.\n{{refend}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.nindb.net/feature/totakas-song-guide/index.html Kazumi Totaka's Song] at [http://www.nindb.net NinDB]\n\n{{Animal Crossing}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Totaka, Kazumi}}\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:Japanese composers]]\n[[Category:Japanese male composers]]\n[[Category:Japanese male voice actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Tokyo]]\n[[Category:Nintendo people]]\n[[Category:Video game composers]]\n", "name_user": "Th1rt3en", "label": "safe", "comment": "rv good faith (?) edits", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kazumi_Totaka"}
{"title_page": "Pristerodontia", "text_new": "{{Automatic taxobox\n| name = Pristerodontia\n| taxon = Pristerodontia\n| fossil_range = [[Late Permian]] \u2013 [[Late Triassic]]\n| image = Oudenodon latirostris.jpg\n| image_caption = Skull of ''[[Oudenodon|Oudenodon latirostris]]''\n| authority = Cluver and King, 1983\n| subdivision_ranks = Clades\n| subdivision =\n* [[Dicynodontoidea]]\n}}\n\n'''Pristerodontia''' is a group of [[dicynodont]] [[therapsid]]s that includes [[Cryptodontia|cryptodontids]], [[Geikiidae|geikiids]], this is the end of an era[[Lystrosauridae|lystrosaurids]], [[Kannemeyeria|kannemeyeriids]], and other related forms. Pristerodontians were one of the few groups of dicynodonts to survive the [[Permiand\u2013Triassic extinction event]], diversifying in the [[Triassic]].<ref name=MMW02>{{cite journal |last=Maisch |first=M.W. |year=2002 |title=A new basal lystrosaurid dicynodont from the Upper Permian of South Africa |journal=Palaeontology |volume=45 |issue=2 |pages=343\u2013359 |doi=10.1111/1475-4983.00240}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Anomodontia|O.}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q7245891}}\n\n[[Category:Dicynodonts]]\n[[Category:Permian synapsids]]\n[[Category:Triassic synapsids]]\n[[Category:Lopingian first appearances]]\n[[Category:Late Triassic extinctions]]\n\n\n{{anomodont-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Automatic taxobox\n| name = Pristerodontia\n| taxon = Pristerodontia\n| fossil_range = [[Late Permian]] \u2013 [[Late Triassic]]\n| image = Oudenodon latirostris.jpg\n| image_caption = Skull of ''[[Oudenodon|Oudenodon latirostris]]''\n| authority = Cluver and King, 1983\n| subdivision_ranks = Clades\n| subdivision =\n* [[Dicynodontoidea]]\n}}\n\n'''Pristerodontia''' is a group of [[dicynodont]] [[therapsid]]s that includes [[Cryptodontia|cryptodontids]], [[Geikiidae|geikiids]], [[Lystrosauridae|lystrosaurids]], [[Kannemeyeria|kannemeyeriids]], and other related forms. Pristerodontians were one of the few groups of dicynodonts to survive the [[Permian\u2013Triassic extinction event]], diversifying in the [[Triassic]].<ref name=MMW02>{{cite journal |last=Maisch |first=M.W. |year=2002 |title=A new basal lystrosaurid dicynodont from the Upper Permian of South Africa |journal=Palaeontology |volume=45 |issue=2 |pages=343\u2013359 |doi=10.1111/1475-4983.00240}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Anomodontia|O.}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q7245891}}\n\n[[Category:Dicynodonts]]\n[[Category:Permian synapsids]]\n[[Category:Triassic synapsids]]\n[[Category:Lopingian first appearances]]\n[[Category:Late Triassic extinctions]]\n\n\n{{anomodont-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Braz vlogs", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pristerodontia"}
